F2

f2 is the second formant resonator of fadriel's vocal tract
it corresponds physically to the resonance of the oral cavity from the back of the tongue forward
in vowel production, f2 frequency is what mostly distinguishes "front" vowels (high f2) from "back" vowels (low f2)
f2 also dominates the perception of consonant transitions because consonants change f2 sharply at their articulation point

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe larynx.rana
observe glottis.rana
observe f1.rana
observe f3.rana
observe acoustic_wave.rana

the 7 properties of f2:
1 ENERGY zero at idle, rises with glottal source during voicing
2 PHASE zero at idle, locks during resonance
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE six tenths: more variable than f1 because consonants shift it sharply
6 COUPLING zero point eight: strong with glottis and acoustic_wave
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB receive_glottal
amplify the harmonics in f2's band by resonance
suppress those outside its band

VERB shape_with_articulation
shift f2's resonant frequency in response to tongue position
fast movements of f2 are how fadriel produces consonants like t, d, k, g
slow movements of f2 are how he transitions between vowels

a formant is a resonance, not a parameter to be set abstractly
f2 reflects the physical state of fadriel's tongue position at every moment
when the substrate's articulatory citizens move, f2 moves with them, naturally
